<TITLE> Sher-e-Bangla's 134th birth anniversary observed Friday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)  Sher-e-Bangla AK Fazlul Huq's 134th birth anniversary was observed Friday with various organisations placing wreaths at his grave and holding discussions on his life and achievements. Sher-e-Bangla Jatiya Smriti Sangsad, Sher-e-Bangla Smriti Academy, Bangabandhu Sangskritik Jote, Jatiya Ganotantrik League, National Awami Party (Bhashani) and Barishal Bibhag Samity will also hold scheduled discussions, milads and other programmes. Sher-e-Bangla AK Fazlul Huq held many high political posts including those of Mayor of Calcutta, chief minister of undivided Bengal and East Bengal, home minister of Pakistan and Governor of East Pakistan. Abul Kashem Fazlul Huq, popularly known as Sher-e-Bangla or Huq Saheb, was born on 26 October 1873, at his maternal uncle's house at Saturia, Bakerganj. His ancestral home was at Chakhar, a village 14 miles from Barisal town. Huq is remembered for his efforts to improve the condition of the Muslim community, to eradicate the poverty of the vast peasant masses and for his generous nature. Sher-e-Bangla Youth Front will present a Sher-e-Bangla award Friday evening at the National Press Club in Dhaka. bdnew
